quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  2,154,"And say not of those who are slain in Allah´s Way (the Way of striving, sacrifice and restraint) (that they are) dead. Nay, they are living; but you do not perceive it"
  2,155,"We will try you with something of fear, and hunger and loss of wealth, and lives and fruits (of toil); but give good tidings to those who patiently persevere"
  2,156,"Who, when there falls on them a calamity say, \"Verily, we are Allah´s and, verily, to Him is our return"
  2,157,"These are they on whom are blessings from their Lord and Mercy, and they it is who receive Guidance"
  2,158,"Verily, Zafa and Merwah (mountains near the Kaaba) are of the beacons (symbols) of Allah, and he who makes the pilgrimage unto the House, or visits it at other times, it is no crime for him to compass them both about; and he who obeys his own Impulse to G"
  2,159,"Verily, those who hide what We have revealed of manifest Signs and of Guidance after We have manifested it to men in the Book, them Allah shall curse, and those entitled to curse shall curse them too"
  2,160,"Save those who turn (repent) and make amends and openly declare the truth; these will I turn to again, for I am Oft-Relenting, Most Merciful"
  2,161,"Verily, those who disbelieve (or reject faith) and die while still in disbelief, on them is the curse of Allah, and of the angels, and of all mankind"
  2,162,"They will dwell therein (in the curse) for ever; the torment shall not be lightened for them, nor shall they have any respite"
  2,163,"Your God is one God; there is no God but He, the Compassionate, the Merciful"